The simmer transfer deals in the English Premier League are getting hotter every day. Leeds United of England have joined the contention with a Ligue 1 club in France, Nice, for the signature of a Nigerian football star, Moses Simon, from Nantes as replacement for Raphinha.
Raphinha is being hunted by Chelsea, Arsenal, and Barcelona, making Leeds begin for search for a replacement.
Moses Simon, 26, is Super Eagles player, and has been prolific in virtually all the national engagements over the years. He is fast on the flanks and has high dribbling skills.
